6519  __ emit_i32_or(new_value.gp(), result_reg.gp(), value.gp());
6520  break;
6521  case kExprArrayAtomicXor:
6522  __ emit_i32_xor(new_value.gp(), result_reg.gp(), value.gp());
6523  break;
6524  case kExprArrayAtomicExchange:
6525  break;
6526  default:
6527  UNREACHABLE();
6528  }
6529  } else if (elem_kind == ValueKind::kI64) {
6530  switch (opcode) {
6531  case kExprArrayAtomicAdd:
6532  __ emit_i64_add(new_value, result_reg, value);
6533  break;
6534  case kExprArrayAtomicSub:
6535  __ emit_i64_sub(new_value, result_reg, value);
6536  break;
6537  case kExprArrayAtomicAnd:
6538  __ emit_i64_and(new_value, result_reg, value);
6539  break;
6540  case kExprArrayAtomicOr:
6541  __ emit_i64_or(new_value, result_reg, value);
6542  break;
6543  case kExprArrayAtomicXor:
6544  __ emit_i64_xor(new_value, result_reg, value);
6545  break;
6546  case kExprArrayAtomicExchange:
6547  break;
6548  default:
6549  UNREACHABLE();
6550  }
6551  } else {
6552  CHECK(is_reference(elem_kind));
6553  CHECK_EQ(opcode, kExprArrayAtomicExchange);
6554  // Nothing to be done here.
6555  }
6556  __ PushRegister(elem_kind, result_reg);
6557  StoreObjectField(decoder, array.gp(), index.gp(),
6558  wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(WasmArray::kHeaderSize),
6559  new_value, false, pinned, elem_kind);
6560  return;
6561  }
6562 #endif // !V8_TARGET_ARCH_IA32
6563 
6564 #ifdef V8_TARGET_ARCH_IA32
6565  // The tagged atomic exchange needs the value register for the write
6566  // barrier.
6567  const bool preserve_value_reg =
6568  opcode == kExprArrayAtomicExchange && is_reference(elem_kind);
6569  LiftoffRegister result_reg =
6570  preserve_value_reg
6571  ? pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(reg_class_for(elem_kind), pinned))
6572  : value;
6573 #else
6574  LiftoffRegister result_reg =
6575  pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(reg_class_for(elem_kind), pinned));
6576 #endif
6577  const int offset = wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(WasmArray::kHeaderSize);
6578  switch (opcode) {
6579  case kExprArrayAtomicAdd:
6580  __ AtomicAdd(array.gp(), index.gp(), offset, value, result_reg,
6581  StoreType::ForValueKind(elem_kind), false);
6582  break;
6583  case kExprArrayAtomicSub:
6584  __ AtomicSub(array.gp(), index.gp(), offset, value, result_reg,
6585  StoreType::ForValueKind(elem_kind), false);
6586  break;
6587  case kExprArrayAtomicAnd:
6588  __ AtomicAnd(array.gp(), index.gp(), offset, value, result_reg,
6589  StoreType::ForValueKind(elem_kind), false);
6590  break;
6591  case kExprArrayAtomicOr:
6592  __ AtomicOr(array.gp(), index.gp(), offset, value, result_reg,
6593  StoreType::ForValueKind(elem_kind), false);
6594  break;
6595  case kExprArrayAtomicXor:
6596  __ AtomicXor(array.gp(), index.gp(), offset, value, result_reg,
6597  StoreType::ForValueKind(elem_kind), false);
6598  break;
6599  case kExprArrayAtomicExchange:
6600  if (is_reference(elem_kind)) {
6601  __ AtomicExchangeTaggedPointer(array.gp(), index.gp(), offset, value,
6602  result_reg, pinned);
6603  break;
6604  }
6605  __ AtomicExchange(array.gp(), index.gp(), offset, value, result_reg,
6606  StoreType::ForValueKind(elem_kind), false);
6607  break;
6608  default:
6609  UNREACHABLE();
6610  }

6612  }

2589  BindFirst(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_i64_set_cond, kNotEqual));
2590  case kExprI64LtS:
2591  return EmitBinOp<kI64, kI32>(
2592  BindFirst(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_i64_set_cond, kLessThan));
2593  case kExprI64LtU:
2594  return EmitBinOp<kI64, kI32>(
2595  BindFirst(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_i64_set_cond, kUnsignedLessThan));
2596  case kExprI64GtS:
2597  return EmitBinOp<kI64, kI32>(
2598  BindFirst(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_i64_set_cond, kGreaterThan));
2599  case kExprI64GtU:
2600  return EmitBinOp<kI64, kI32>(BindFirst(
2601  &LiftoffAssembler::emit_i64_set_cond, kUnsignedGreaterThan));
2602  case kExprI64LeS:
2603  return EmitBinOp<kI64, kI32>(
2604  BindFirst(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_i64_set_cond, kLessThanEqual));
2605  case kExprI64LeU:
2606  return EmitBinOp<kI64, kI32>(BindFirst(
2607  &LiftoffAssembler::emit_i64_set_cond, kUnsignedLessThanEqual));
2608  case kExprI64GeS:
2609  return EmitBinOp<kI64, kI32>(
2610  BindFirst(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_i64_set_cond, kGreaterThanEqual));
2611  case kExprI64GeU:
2612  return EmitBinOp<kI64, kI32>(BindFirst(
2613  &LiftoffAssembler::emit_i64_set_cond, kUnsignedGreaterThanEqual));
2614  case kExprF32Eq:
2615  return EmitBinOp<kF32, kI32>(
2616  BindFirst(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_f32_set_cond, kEqual));
2617  case kExprF32Ne:
2618  return EmitBinOp<kF32, kI32>(
2619  BindFirst(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_f32_set_cond, kNotEqual));
2620  case kExprF32Lt:
2621  return EmitBinOp<kF32, kI32>(
2622  BindFirst(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_f32_set_cond, kUnsignedLessThan));
2623  case kExprF32Gt:
2624  return EmitBinOp<kF32, kI32>(BindFirst(
2625  &LiftoffAssembler::emit_f32_set_cond, kUnsignedGreaterThan));
2626  case kExprF32Le:
2627  return EmitBinOp<kF32, kI32>(BindFirst(
2628  &LiftoffAssembler::emit_f32_set_cond, kUnsignedLessThanEqual));
2629  case kExprF32Ge:
2630  return EmitBinOp<kF32, kI32>(BindFirst(
2631  &LiftoffAssembler::emit_f32_set_cond, kUnsignedGreaterThanEqual));
2632  case kExprF64Eq:
2633  return EmitBinOp<kF64, kI32>(
2634  BindFirst(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_f64_set_cond, kEqual));
2635  case kExprF64Ne:
2636  return EmitBinOp<kF64, kI32>(
2637  BindFirst(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_f64_set_cond, kNotEqual));
2638  case kExprF64Lt:
2639  return EmitBinOp<kF64, kI32>(
2640  BindFirst(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_f64_set_cond, kUnsignedLessThan));
2641  case kExprF64Gt:
2642  return EmitBinOp<kF64, kI32>(BindFirst(
2643  &LiftoffAssembler::emit_f64_set_cond, kUnsignedGreaterThan));
2644  case kExprF64Le:
2645  return EmitBinOp<kF64, kI32>(BindFirst(
2646  &LiftoffAssembler::emit_f64_set_cond, kUnsignedLessThanEqual));
2647  case kExprF64Ge:
2648  return EmitBinOp<kF64, kI32>(BindFirst(
2649  &LiftoffAssembler::emit_f64_set_cond, kUnsignedGreaterThanEqual));
2650  case kExprI32Shl:
2651  return EmitBinOpImm<kI32, kI32>(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_i32_shl,
2652  &LiftoffAssembler::emit_i32_shli);
2653  case kExprI32ShrS:
2654  return EmitBinOpImm<kI32, kI32>(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_i32_sar,
2655  &LiftoffAssembler::emit_i32_sari);
2656  case kExprI32ShrU:
2657  return EmitBinOpImm<kI32, kI32>(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_i32_shr,
2658  &LiftoffAssembler::emit_i32_shri);
2659  case kExprI32Rol:
2660  return EmitBitRotationCCall<kI32, ExternalReference::wasm_word32_rol>();
2661  case kExprI32Ror:
2662  return EmitBitRotationCCall<kI32, ExternalReference::wasm_word32_ror>();
2663  case kExprI64Shl:
2664  return EmitI64Shift(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_i64_shl,
2665  &LiftoffAssembler::emit_i64_shli);
2666  case kExprI64ShrS:
2667  return EmitI64Shift(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_i64_sar,
2668  &LiftoffAssembler::emit_i64_sari);
2669  case kExprI64ShrU:
2670  return EmitI64Shift(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_i64_shr,
2671  &LiftoffAssembler::emit_i64_shri);
2672  case kExprI64Rol:
2673  return EmitBitRotationCCall<kI64, ExternalReference::wasm_word64_rol>();
2674  case kExprI64Ror:
2675  return EmitBitRotationCCall<kI64, ExternalReference::wasm_word64_ror>();
2676  case kExprF32Add:
2677  return EmitBinOp<kF32, kF32>(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_f32_add);
2678  case kExprF32Sub:
2679  return EmitBinOp<kF32, kF32>(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_f32_sub);
2680  case kExprF32Mul:
2681  return EmitBinOp<kF32, kF32>(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_f32_mul);
2682  case kExprF32Div:
2683  return EmitBinOp<kF32, kF32>(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_f32_div);
2684  case kExprF32Min:
2685  return EmitBinOp<kF32, kF32>(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_f32_min);
2686  case kExprF32Max:
2687  return EmitBinOp<kF32, kF32>(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_f32_max);
2688  case kExprF32CopySign:
2689  return EmitBinOp<kF32, kF32>(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_f32_copysign);
2690  case kExprF64Add:
2691  return EmitBinOp<kF64, kF64>(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_f64_add);
2692  case kExprF64Sub:
2693  return EmitBinOp<kF64, kF64>(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_f64_sub);
2694  case kExprF64Mul:
2695  return EmitBinOp<kF64, kF64>(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_f64_mul);
2696  case kExprF64Div:
2697  return EmitBinOp<kF64, kF64>(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_f64_div);
2698  case kExprF64Min:
2699  return EmitBinOp<kF64, kF64>(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_f64_min);
2700  case kExprF64Max:
2701  return EmitBinOp<kF64, kF64>(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_f64_max);
2702  case kExprF64CopySign:
2703  return EmitBinOp<kF64, kF64>(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_f64_copysign);
2704  case kExprI32DivS:
2705  return EmitBinOp<kI32, kI32>([this, decoder](LiftoffRegister dst,
2706  LiftoffRegister lhs,
2707  LiftoffRegister rhs) {
2708  AddOutOfLineTrapDeprecated(decoder, Builtin::kThrowWasmTrapDivByZero);
2709  // Adding the second trap might invalidate the pointer returned for
2710  // the first one, thus get both pointers afterwards.
2711  AddOutOfLineTrapDeprecated(decoder,
2712  Builtin::kThrowWasmTrapDivUnrepresentable);
2713  Label* div_by_zero = out_of_line_code_.end()[-2].label.get();
2714  Label* div_unrepresentable = out_of_line_code_.end()[-1].label.get();
2715  __ emit_i32_divs(dst.gp(), lhs.gp(), rhs.gp(), div_by_zero,
2716  div_unrepresentable);
2717  });
2718  case kExprI32DivU:
2719  return EmitBinOp<kI32, kI32>([this, decoder](LiftoffRegister dst,
2720  LiftoffRegister lhs,
2721  LiftoffRegister rhs) {
2722  Label* div_by_zero = AddOutOfLineTrapDeprecated(
2723  decoder, Builtin::kThrowWasmTrapDivByZero);
2724  __ emit_i32_divu(dst.gp(), lhs.gp(), rhs.gp(), div_by_zero);
2725  });
2726  case kExprI32RemS:
2727  return EmitBinOp<kI32, kI32>([this, decoder](LiftoffRegister dst,
2728  LiftoffRegister lhs,
2729  LiftoffRegister rhs) {
2730  Label* rem_by_zero = AddOutOfLineTrapDeprecated(
2731  decoder, Builtin::kThrowWasmTrapRemByZero);
2732  __ emit_i32_rems(dst.gp(), lhs.gp(), rhs.gp(), rem_by_zero);
2733  });
2734  case kExprI32RemU:
2735  return EmitBinOp<kI32, kI32>([this, decoder](LiftoffRegister dst,
2736  LiftoffRegister lhs,
2737  LiftoffRegister rhs) {
2738  Label* rem_by_zero = AddOutOfLineTrapDeprecated(
2739  decoder, Builtin::kThrowWasmTrapRemByZero);
2740  __ emit_i32_remu(dst.gp(), lhs.gp(), rhs.gp(), rem_by_zero);
2741  });
2742  case kExprI64DivS:
2743  return EmitBinOp<kI64, kI64>([this, decoder](LiftoffRegister dst,
2744  LiftoffRegister lhs,
2745  LiftoffRegister rhs) {
2746  AddOutOfLineTrapDeprecated(decoder, Builtin::kThrowWasmTrapDivByZero);
2747  // Adding the second trap might invalidate the pointer returned for
2748  // the first one, thus get both pointers afterwards.
2749  AddOutOfLineTrapDeprecated(decoder,
2750  Builtin::kThrowWasmTrapDivUnrepresentable);
2751  Label* div_by_zero = out_of_line_code_.end()[-2].label.get();
2752  Label* div_unrepresentable = out_of_line_code_.end()[-1].label.get();
2753  if (!__ emit_i64_divs(dst, lhs, rhs, div_by_zero,
2754  div_unrepresentable)) {
2755  ExternalReference ext_ref = ExternalReference::wasm_int64_div();
2756  EmitDivOrRem64CCall(dst, lhs, rhs, ext_ref, div_by_zero,
2757  div_unrepresentable);
2758  }
2759  });
2760  case kExprI64DivU:
2761  return EmitBinOp<kI64, kI64>([this, decoder](LiftoffRegister dst,
2762  LiftoffRegister lhs,
2763  LiftoffRegister rhs) {
2764  Label* div_by_zero = AddOutOfLineTrapDeprecated(
2765  decoder, Builtin::kThrowWasmTrapDivByZero);
2766  if (!__ emit_i64_divu(dst, lhs, rhs, div_by_zero)) {
2767  ExternalReference ext_ref = ExternalReference::wasm_uint64_div();
2768  EmitDivOrRem64CCall(dst, lhs, rhs, ext_ref, div_by_zero);
2769  }
2770  });
2771  case kExprI64RemS:
2772  return EmitBinOp<kI64, kI64>([this, decoder](LiftoffRegister dst,
2773  LiftoffRegister lhs,
2774  LiftoffRegister rhs) {
2775  Label* rem_by_zero = AddOutOfLineTrapDeprecated(
2776  decoder, Builtin::kThrowWasmTrapRemByZero);
2777  if (!__ emit_i64_rems(dst, lhs, rhs, rem_by_zero)) {
2778  ExternalReference ext_ref = ExternalReference::wasm_int64_mod();
2779  EmitDivOrRem64CCall(dst, lhs, rhs, ext_ref, rem_by_zero);
2780  }
2781  });
2782  case kExprI64RemU:
2783  return EmitBinOp<kI64, kI64>([this, decoder](LiftoffRegister dst,
2784  LiftoffRegister lhs,
2785  LiftoffRegister rhs) {
2786  Label* rem_by_zero = AddOutOfLineTrapDeprecated(
2787  decoder, Builtin::kThrowWasmTrapRemByZero);
2788  if (!__ emit_i64_remu(dst, lhs, rhs, rem_by_zero)) {
2789  ExternalReference ext_ref = ExternalReference::wasm_uint64_mod();
2790  EmitDivOrRem64CCall(dst, lhs, rhs, ext_ref, rem_by_zero);
2791  }
2792  });
2793  case kExprRefEq: {
2794 #if defined(V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS)
2795  // In pointer compression, we smi-corrupt (the upper bits of a
2796  // Smi are arbitrary). So, we should only compare the lower 32 bits.
2797  return EmitBinOp<kRefNull, kI32>(
2798  BindFirst(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_i32_set_cond, kEqual));
2799 #else
2800  return EmitBinOp<kRefNull, kI32>(
2801  BindFirst(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_ptrsize_set_cond, kEqual));
2802 #endif
2803  }
2804 
2805  default:
2806  UNREACHABLE();
2807  }
2808  }

9639  __ emit_u32_to_uintptr(table_size.gp_reg(), table_size.gp_reg());
9640  comparison_type = kIntPtrKind;
9641  }
9642  __ emit_cond_jump(kUnsignedLessThanEqual, out_of_bounds.label(),
9643  comparison_type, table_size.gp_reg(), index_reg,
9644  out_of_bounds.frozen());
9645  }
9646  } else {
9647  DCHECK_EQ(max_table_size, table->initial_size);
9648  if (is_static_index) {
9649  DCHECK_LT(index_slot.i32_const(), max_table_size);
9650  } else if (Is64() && table->is_table64()) {
9651  // On 32-bit, this is the same as below, so include the `Is64()` test
9652  // to statically tell the compiler to skip this branch.
9653  // Note: {max_table_size} will be sign-extended, which is fine because
9654  // the MSB is known to be 0 (asserted by the static_assert below).
9655  static_assert(kV8MaxWasmTableSize <= kMaxInt);
9656  __ emit_ptrsize_cond_jumpi(kUnsignedGreaterThanEqual,
9657  out_of_bounds.label(), index_reg,
9658  max_table_size, out_of_bounds.frozen());
9659  } else {
9660  __ emit_i32_cond_jumpi(kUnsignedGreaterThanEqual,
9661  out_of_bounds.label(), index_reg,
9662  max_table_size, out_of_bounds.frozen());
9663  }
9664  }
9665  }
9666 
9667  // If the function index is dynamic, compute a pointer to the dispatch table
9668  // entry. Otherwise remember the static offset from the dispatch table to
9669  // add it to later loads from that table.
9670  ScopedTempRegister dispatch_table_base{std::move(dispatch_table)};
9671  int dispatch_table_offset = 0;
9672  if (is_static_index) {
9673  // Avoid potential integer overflow here by excluding too large
9674  // (statically OOB) indexes. This code is not reached for statically OOB
9675  // indexes anyway.
9676  dispatch_table_offset =
9677  statically_oob
9678  ? 0
9679  : wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(
9680  WasmDispatchTable::OffsetOf(index_slot.i32_const()));
9681  } else {
9682  // TODO(clemensb): Produce better code for this (via more specialized
9683  // platform-specific methods?).
9684 
9685  Register entry_offset = index_reg;
9686  // After this computation we don't need the index register any more. If
9687  // there is no other user we can overwrite it.
9688  bool index_reg_still_used =
9689  __ cache_state() -> get_use_count(LiftoffRegister{index_reg}) > 1;
9690  if (index_reg_still_used) entry_offset = temps.Acquire(kGpReg).gp();

9694  __ emit_ptrsize_muli(entry_offset, entry_offset,
9695  WasmDispatchTable::kEntrySize);
9696  __ emit_ptrsize_add(dispatch_table_base.gp_reg(),
9697  dispatch_table_base.gp_reg(), entry_offset);
9698  if (index_reg_still_used) temps.Return(std::move(entry_offset));
9699  dispatch_table_offset =
9700  wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(WasmDispatchTable::kEntriesOffset);
9701  }
9702 
9703  bool needs_type_check = !EquivalentTypes(
9704  table->type.AsNonNull(), ValueType::Ref(imm.sig_imm.heap_type()),
9705  decoder->module_);
9706  bool needs_null_check = table->type.is_nullable();
9707 
9708  // We do both the type check and the null check by checking the signature,
9709  // so this shares most code. For the null check we then only check if the
9710  // stored signature is != -1.
9711  if (needs_type_check || needs_null_check) {
9712  SCOPED_CODE_COMMENT(needs_type_check ? "Check signature"
9713  : "Check for null entry");
9714  ScopedTempRegister real_sig_id{temps, kGpReg};
9715 
9716  // Load the signature from the dispatch table.
9717  __ Load(real_sig_id.reg(), dispatch_table_base.gp_reg(), no_reg,
9718  dispatch_table_offset + WasmDispatchTable::kSigBias,
9719  LoadType::kI32Load);
9720 
9721  // Compare against expected signature.
9722  // Since Liftoff code is never serialized (hence not reused across
9723  // isolates / processes) the canonical signature ID is a static integer.
9724  CanonicalTypeIndex canonical_sig_id =
9725  decoder->module_->canonical_sig_id(imm.sig_imm.index);
9726  OolTrapLabel sig_mismatch =
9727  AddOutOfLineTrap(decoder, Builtin::kThrowWasmTrapFuncSigMismatch);
9728  __ DropValues(1);
9729 
9730  if (!needs_type_check) {
9731  DCHECK(needs_null_check);
9732  // Only check for -1 (nulled table entry).
9733  __ emit_i32_cond_jumpi(kEqual, sig_mismatch.label(),
9734  real_sig_id.gp_reg(), -1, sig_mismatch.frozen());
9735  } else if (!decoder->module_->type(imm.sig_imm.index).is_final) {
9736  Label success_label;
9737  __ emit_i32_cond_jumpi(kEqual, &success_label, real_sig_id.gp_reg(),
9738  canonical_sig_id.index, sig_mismatch.frozen());
9739  if (needs_null_check) {
9740  __ emit_i32_cond_jumpi(kEqual, sig_mismatch.label(),
9741  real_sig_id.gp_reg(), -1,
9742  sig_mismatch.frozen());
9743  }
9744  ScopedTempRegister real_rtt{temps, kGpReg};
9745  __ LoadFullPointer(
9746  real_rtt.gp_reg(), kRootRegister,
9747  IsolateData::root_slot_offset(RootIndex::kWasmCanonicalRtts));
9748  __ LoadTaggedPointer(
9749  real_rtt.gp_reg(), real_rtt.gp_reg(), real_sig_id.gp_reg(),
9750  ObjectAccess::ToTagged(OFFSET_OF_DATA_START(WeakFixedArray)),
9751  nullptr, true);
9752  // real_sig_id is not used any more.
9753  real_sig_id.Reset();
9754  // Remove the weak reference tag.
9755  if constexpr (kSystemPointerSize == 4) {
9756  __ emit_i32_andi(real_rtt.gp_reg(), real_rtt.gp_reg(),
9757  static_cast<int32_t>(~kWeakHeapObjectMask));
9758  } else {
9759  __ emit_i64_andi(real_rtt.reg(), real_rtt.reg(),
9760  static_cast<int32_t>(~kWeakHeapObjectMask));
9761  }
9762  // Constant-time subtyping check: load exactly one candidate RTT from
9763  // the supertypes list.
9764  // Step 1: load the WasmTypeInfo.
9765  constexpr int kTypeInfoOffset = wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(
9766  Map::kConstructorOrBackPointerOrNativeContextOffset);
9767  ScopedTempRegister type_info{std::move(real_rtt)};
9768  __ LoadTaggedPointer(type_info.gp_reg(), type_info.gp_reg(), no_reg,
9769  kTypeInfoOffset);
9770  // Step 2: check the list's length if needed.
9771  uint32_t rtt_depth =
9772  GetSubtypingDepth(decoder->module_, imm.sig_imm.index);
9773  if (rtt_depth >= kMinimumSupertypeArraySize) {
9774  ScopedTempRegister list_length{temps, kGpReg};

9777  __ LoadSmiAsInt32(list_length.reg(), type_info.gp_reg(), offset);
9778  __ emit_i32_cond_jumpi(kUnsignedLessThanEqual, sig_mismatch.label(),
9779  list_length.gp_reg(), rtt_depth,
9780  sig_mismatch.frozen());
9781  }
9782  // Step 3: load the candidate list slot, and compare it.
9783  ScopedTempRegister maybe_match{std::move(type_info)};
9784  __ LoadTaggedPointer(
9785  maybe_match.gp_reg(), maybe_match.gp_reg(), no_reg,
9786  ObjectAccess::ToTagged(WasmTypeInfo::kSupertypesOffset +
9787  rtt_depth * kTaggedSize));
9788  ScopedTempRegister formal_rtt{temps, kGpReg};
9789  // Instead of {pinned}, we use {kGpCacheRegList} as the list of pinned
9790  // registers, to prevent any attempt to cache the instance, which would
9791  // be incompatible with the {FREEZE_STATE} that is in effect here.

9797  imm.sig_imm.index.index));

9799  formal_rtt.gp_reg(), maybe_match.gp_reg(),
9800  sig_mismatch.frozen());
9801 
9802  __ bind(&success_label);
9803  } else {
9804  __ emit_i32_cond_jumpi(kNotEqual, sig_mismatch.label(),
9805  real_sig_id.gp_reg(), canonical_sig_id.index,
9806  sig_mismatch.frozen());
9807  }
9808  } else {
9809  __ DropValues(1);
9810  }

9814

9839  // The number of call instructions (and hence feedback vector slots) is
9840  // capped by the number of instructions, which is capped by the maximum
9841  // function body size.

9851  // as parameters and return them unchanged) as `CallBuiltin` otherwise
9852  // clobbers them. (The spilling code in `SpillAllRegisters` is only
9853  // aware of registers used on Liftoff's abstract value stack, not the

9856  // each call_indirect by moving the target and ref lookup into the
9857  // builtin as well.
9858  // However, then we would either (a) need to replicate the optimizations
9859  // above for static indices etc., which increases code duplication and
9860  // maintenance cost, or (b) regress performance even more than the
9861  // builtin call itself already does.

9863  // amount of code when inlining is enabled vs. not.

9865  VarState implicit_arg_var(kRef, LiftoffRegister(implicit_arg), 0);

5236  &LiftoffAssembler::emit_i16x8_dot_i8x16_i7x16_s);
5237  case wasm::kExprI32x4DotI8x16I7x16AddS: {
5238  // There is no helper for an instruction with 3 SIMD operands
5239  // and we do not expect to add any more, so inlining it here.
5240  static constexpr RegClass res_rc = reg_class_for(kS128);
5241  LiftoffRegList pinned;
5242  LiftoffRegister acc = pinned.set(__ PopToRegister(pinned));
5243  LiftoffRegister rhs = pinned.set(__ PopToRegister(pinned));
5244  LiftoffRegister lhs = pinned.set(__ PopToRegister(pinned));
5245 #if V8_TARGET_ARCH_X64 || V8_TARGET_ARCH_IA32
5246  // x86 platforms save a move when dst == acc, so prefer that.
5247  LiftoffRegister dst =
5248  __ GetUnusedRegister(res_rc, {acc}, LiftoffRegList{lhs, rhs});
5249 #else
5250  // On other platforms, for simplicity, we ensure that none of the
5251  // registers alias. (If we cared, it would probably be feasible to
5252  // allow {dst} to alias with {lhs} or {rhs}, but that'd be brittle.)
5253  LiftoffRegister dst = __ GetUnusedRegister(res_rc, pinned);
5254 #endif
5255 
5256  __ emit_i32x4_dot_i8x16_i7x16_add_s(dst, lhs, rhs, acc);
5257  __ PushRegister(kS128, dst);
5258  return;
5259  }
5260  default:
5261  UNREACHABLE();
5262  }
5263  }

7951  if (module->type(target_type.ref_index()).is_final ||
7952  target_type.is_exact()) {
7953  // In this case, simply check for map equality.
7954  __ emit_cond_jump(kNotEqual, no_match, ValueKind::kRef, tmp1, rtt_reg,
7955  frozen);
7956  } else {
7957  // Check for rtt equality, and if not, check if the rtt is a struct/array
7958  // rtt.
7959  __ emit_cond_jump(kEqual, &match, ValueKind::kRef, tmp1, rtt_reg, frozen);
7960 
7961  if (is_cast_from_any) {
7962  // Check for map being a map for a wasm object (struct, array, func).
7963  __ Load(LiftoffRegister(scratch2), tmp1, no_reg,
7964  wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(Map::kInstanceTypeOffset),
7965  LoadType::kI32Load16U);
7966  __ emit_i32_subi(scratch2, scratch2, FIRST_WASM_OBJECT_TYPE);
7967  __ emit_i32_cond_jumpi(kUnsignedGreaterThan, no_match, scratch2,
7968  LAST_WASM_OBJECT_TYPE - FIRST_WASM_OBJECT_TYPE,
7969  frozen);
7970  }
7971 
7972  // Constant-time subtyping check: load exactly one candidate RTT from the
7973  // supertypes list.
7974  // Step 1: load the WasmTypeInfo into {tmp1}.
7975  constexpr int kTypeInfoOffset = wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(
7976  Map::kConstructorOrBackPointerOrNativeContextOffset);
7977  __ LoadTaggedPointer(tmp1, tmp1, no_reg, kTypeInfoOffset);
7978  // Step 2: check the list's length if needed.
7979  uint32_t rtt_depth = GetSubtypingDepth(module, target_type.ref_index());
7980  if (rtt_depth >= kMinimumSupertypeArraySize) {
7981  LiftoffRegister list_length(scratch2);
7982  int offset =
7983  ObjectAccess::ToTagged(WasmTypeInfo::kSupertypesLengthOffset);
7984  __ LoadSmiAsInt32(list_length, tmp1, offset);
7985  __ emit_i32_cond_jumpi(kUnsignedLessThanEqual, no_match,
7986  list_length.gp(), rtt_depth, frozen);
7987  }
7988  // Step 3: load the candidate list slot into {tmp1}, and compare it.
7989  __ LoadTaggedPointer(
7990  tmp1, tmp1, no_reg,
7991  ObjectAccess::ToTagged(WasmTypeInfo::kSupertypesOffset +
7992  rtt_depth * kTaggedSize));
7993  __ emit_cond_jump(kNotEqual, no_match, ValueKind::kRef, tmp1, rtt_reg,
7994  frozen);
7995  }
7996 
7997  // Fall through to {match}.
7998  __ bind(&match);
7999  }

2323  DCHECK(decoder->lookahead(0, kExprI32Eqz));
2324  if ((decoder->lookahead(1, kExprBrIf) ||
2325  decoder->lookahead(1, kExprIf)) &&
2326  !for_debugging_) {
2327  DCHECK(!has_outstanding_op());
2328  outstanding_op_ = kExprI32Eqz;
2329  break;
2330  }
2331  return EmitUnOp<kI32, kI32>(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_i32_eqz);
2332  case kExprI64Eqz:
2333  return EmitUnOp<kI64, kI32>(&LiftoffAssembler::emit_i64_eqz);
2334  case kExprI32Popcnt:
2335  return EmitUnOp<kI32, kI32>(
2336  [this](LiftoffRegister dst, LiftoffRegister src) {
2337  if (__ emit_i32_popcnt(dst.gp(), src.gp())) return;
2338  LiftoffRegister result =
2339  GenerateCCall(kI32, {VarState{kI32, src, 0}},
2340  ExternalReference::wasm_word32_popcnt());
2341  if (result != dst) __ Move(dst.gp(), result.gp(), kI32);
2342  });
2343  case kExprI64Popcnt:
2344  return EmitUnOp<kI64, kI64>(
2345  [this](LiftoffRegister dst, LiftoffRegister src) {
2346  if (__ emit_i64_popcnt(dst, src)) return;
2347  // The c function returns i32. We will zero-extend later.
2348  LiftoffRegister result =
2349  GenerateCCall(kI32, {VarState{kI64, src, 0}},
2350  ExternalReference::wasm_word64_popcnt());
2351  // Now zero-extend the result to i64.
2352  __ emit_type_conversion(kExprI64UConvertI32, dst, result,
2353  nullptr);
2354  });
2355  case kExprRefIsNull:
2356  // We abuse ref.as_non_null, which isn't otherwise used in this switch, as
2357  // a sentinel for the negation of ref.is_null.
2358  case kExprRefAsNonNull:
2359  return EmitIsNull(opcode, value.type);
2360  case kExprAnyConvertExtern: {
2361  VarState input_state = __ cache_state()->stack_state.back();
2362  const bool is_shared = value.type.is_shared();
2363  CallBuiltin(is_shared ? Builtin::kWasmAnyConvertExternShared
2364  : Builtin::kWasmAnyConvertExtern,
2365  MakeSig::Returns(kRefNull).Params(kRefNull), {input_state},
2366  decoder->position());
2367  __ DropValues(1);
2368  __ PushRegister(kRef, LiftoffRegister(kReturnRegister0));
2369  return;
2370  }
2371  case kExprExternConvertAny: {
2372  LiftoffRegList pinned;
2373  LiftoffRegister ref = pinned.set(__ PopToModifiableRegister(pinned));
2374  LiftoffRegister null = __ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned);
2375  LoadNullValueForCompare(null.gp(), pinned, kWasmAnyRef);
2376  Label label;
2377  {
2378  FREEZE_STATE(frozen);
2379  __ emit_cond_jump(kNotEqual, &label, kRefNull, ref.gp(), null.gp(),
2380  frozen);
2381  LoadNullValue(ref.gp(), kWasmExternRef);
2382  __ bind(&label);
2383  }
2384  __ PushRegister(kRefNull, ref);
2385  return;
2386  }
2387  default:
2388  UNREACHABLE();
2389  }
2390 #undef CASE_I32_UNOP
2391 #undef CASE_I64_UNOP
2392 #undef CASE_FLOAT_UNOP
2393 #undef CASE_FLOAT_UNOP_WITH_CFALLBACK
2394 #undef CASE_TYPE_CONVERSION
